 ### Proof
 The graphs labelled (3), (4), and (5) are all invertible since no horizontal line intersects the graph in more than one place. In other words, for each real number $y$ there is at most one real number $x$ with $f(x)=y$.
 The first graph does not satisfy this condition.
 Thus the product of the labels corresponding to invertible functions is $3\times 4\times 5=\boxed{60}$.
